{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"30ea8ae6-fee9-4bd5-afe7-27777ba68822","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Install the SDK** — Download .NET 11 SDK from [dot.net](https://dot.net/download) or update your CI/CD tooling.\n\n**5. Check for breaking changes** — Review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any deprecated APIs or NuGet packages that ship a new major version targeting `net11.0`.\n\nAfter making the changes, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5329fed8-9260-411c-b89f-d57a1d062f9f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":335,"requestId":"6C81:F41F2:E45225:10BFF01:69FE9333"},"id":"a4223171-6478-4c78-9d80-e8b6adc2cb2a","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:51:54.985Z","parentId":"998e75d3-676f-4012-80cd-f9630b2dc991"}
